  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This cohort study aims to assess the quality of life (or welfare) related to the health of
      children and adolescents with an non genetics auto-inflammatory disease PFAPA or Marshall
      syndrome to compare it to children or adolescents with recurrent fever genetics of Familial
      Mediterranean fever (FMF) in order to improve their overall care.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
